<!doctype html>
<html>
{{> head }}
<body id="index">
  {{> header }}
  <div class="content">
    <section id="subtitle">
      <h1>The fastest way to collaborate on code.</h1>
    </section>
    <section id="get-the-app">
      <button>get the app</button>
      <img src="" alt="app image">
    </section>
    <section id="value-prop">
      <h2>Why radicle</h2>
      <p>It's not easy to switch to something new, but here's why you should</p>
      <div class="container">
        <div>
          {{> leaf }}
          <h2>Easy to use</h2>
          <p>
            The best interface for collaborating on code, period. Trust us, we’ve tried them all.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          {{> leaf }}
          <h2>Peer-to-peer</h2>
          <p>
            Work with friends privately from your computer to their computer. No in-betweens.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          {{> leaf }}
          <h2>Local-first</h2>
          <p>
            Can’t lose access to your data if it was never on a large US corporation’s servers.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="get-app">
        <p>sound interesting?</p>
        <button>get the app</button>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section id="tech">
      <h2>The tech behind radicle</h2>
      <p>Radicle is a sovereign stack for code collaboration</p>
      <div class="container">
        <div>
          {{> leaf }}
          <h2>registry</h2>
          <p>
            Radicle uses a decentralized identity layer called Registry.
          </p>
          <a href="">Learn more about Registry -></a>
        </div>
        <div>
          {{> leaf }}
          <h2>link</h2>
          <p>
            For collaboration, Radicle uses Link, a peer-to-peer replication protocol around git.
          </p>
          <a href="">Learn more about link -></a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <button>build your own app</button>
    </section>
  </div>
  {{> footer }}
</body>
</html>
